snippet.textDisplay: Deontay is speaking purely Off adrenaline. I promise you in a couple days he will realize just how much his corner saved him. I have trained majority of my life and I’m telling you a shot to the ear is one of the worst shots to take. It affects your vision, balance, and awareness. Wilder was one punch away from never getting back up, I was honestly scared for him. He is a fighter not a boxer but he can become a polished boxer with the right staff. He is like a basketball player who only knows how to dribble and use his right. He can get over this hurdle but he needs to see all the weak spots in his game plan and boxing style. So many analysts have no idea what they are talking about. Fury being heavier is not a disadvantage when you have a huge frame being 6’-9”. Wilder can get heavier and should have because he is also 6’-7” with a large frame. Fury bullied him because of this since Wilder is not a back foot fighter, the weight difference was a huge advantage for Fury. His corner absolutely saved him from a career ending injury, the ref was watching Wilder like a hawk and Wilder was constantly using the ropes to stabilize himself. Who cares about a lose all that matters is he goes back to the lab and comes up with a new formula. Nobody cares about loses mostly all the Hall of Famers have a lose but their legacy is cemented because of how they fought. If Wilder becomes a polished fighter he can become one of the Greats of heavyweight boxing. His career is not over and it was definitely saved by his corner, hopefully he realizes that.
